          "source_html": "<div class=\"big-section\"><div class=\"group-instruction\"><p><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><strong>Questions 14 - 19</strong></span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><br/></span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\">Look at the seven <span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;; text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">paragraphs</span>&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><strong>(A - G)</strong></span><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\">. Which paragraph contains the following information?</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\">Choose the correct letter </span><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><strong>(A - G)</strong></span><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\">. You may choose any letter more than once.</span></p></div>\r\n    <div class=\"matrix-container\">\r\n        <table>\r\n            <thead><tr><th class=\"corner-header\">Question / Paragraph</th><th>A</th><th>B</th><th>C</th><th>D</th><th>E</th><th>F</th><th>G</th></tr></thead>\r\n            <tbody>\r\n        <tr class=\"q-row\">\r\n            <td class=\"q-text-cell\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-q-wrapper\">\r\n                    <span class=\"matrix-num\">14</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"matrix-content\"><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>14</strong> a time when a transport system became an inspiration for artists</p></div>\r\n                    <button class=\"mini-btn\">🔍</button>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_14\" value=\"A\" data-zyz-question=\"q14\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_14\" value=\"B\" data-zyz-question=\"q14\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_14\" value=\"C\" data-zyz-question=\"q14\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_14\" value=\"D\" data-zyz-question=\"q14\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_14\" value=\"E\" data-zyz-question=\"q14\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_14\" value=\"F\" data-zyz-question=\"q14\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_14\" value=\"G\" data-zyz-question=\"q14\"></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr class=\"ans-row-hidden\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n            <td colspan=\"8\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-analysis\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-key\">✅ 正确答案：E</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-body\"><p>审题：题目问的是哪个段落讲述了交通系统成为艺术家的灵感来源。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键信息：“transport system”和“inspiration”</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文：E段，“In the 19th century, the railways were another feat of engineering which captured the imagination of painters, and the steam engine in the distance of a landscape became as much a part of it as the herd of cows in the foreground.”</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路：文章中E段提到19世纪铁路工程吸引了画家的想象力，蒸汽火车成为风景画的一部分。</p><p><br/></p><p>同义替换：transport system=railways；inspiration=imagination</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        \r\n        <tr class=\"q-row\">\r\n            <td class=\"q-text-cell\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-q-wrapper\">\r\n                    <span class=\"matrix-num\">15</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"matrix-content\"><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>15</strong>&nbsp;a reference to the current trend of including artists in engineering projects</p></div>\r\n                    <button class=\"mini-btn\">🔍</button>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_15\" value=\"A\" data-zyz-question=\"q15\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_15\" value=\"B\" data-zyz-question=\"q15\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_15\" value=\"C\" data-zyz-question=\"q15\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_15\" value=\"D\" data-zyz-question=\"q15\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_15\" value=\"E\" data-zyz-question=\"q15\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_15\" value=\"F\" data-zyz-question=\"q15\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_15\" value=\"G\" data-zyz-question=\"q15\"></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr class=\"ans-row-hidden\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n            <td colspan=\"8\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-analysis\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-key\">✅ 正确答案：G</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-body\"><p>审题：题目问的是哪个段落讲述了当前将艺术家纳入工程项目的趋势。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键信息：“current trend”和“including artists in engineering projects”</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文：G段，“Increasingly, commissioners of bridges in the US are looking to such individuals, to teams of engineers and architects who work with artists.”</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路：文章中G段提到，美国桥梁的委托人越来越倾向于寻找与艺术家合作的工程师和建筑师团队。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        \r\n        <tr class=\"q-row\">\r\n            <td class=\"q-text-cell\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-q-wrapper\">\r\n                    <span class=\"matrix-num\">16</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"matrix-content\"><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>16</strong> reasons for the idea that art and engineering are difficult to combine</p></div>\r\n                    <button class=\"mini-btn\">🔍</button>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_16\" value=\"A\" data-zyz-question=\"q16\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_16\" value=\"B\" data-zyz-question=\"q16\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_16\" value=\"C\" data-zyz-question=\"q16\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_16\" value=\"D\" data-zyz-question=\"q16\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_16\" value=\"E\" data-zyz-question=\"q16\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_16\" value=\"F\" data-zyz-question=\"q16\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_16\" value=\"G\" data-zyz-question=\"q16\"></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr class=\"ans-row-hidden\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n            <td colspan=\"8\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-analysis\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-key\">✅ 正确答案：A</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-body\"><p style=\"text-align: left;\">审题题目问的是哪个段落讲述了艺术与工程难以结合的原因。</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><br/></p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">定位关键信息：“reasons”和“combine”</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><br/></p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">对应原文：A段，“The relationship between art and engineering has seldom been easy or consistent.”</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><br/></p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">解题思路：文章中A段提到艺术与工程之间的关系很少是轻松或一致的。</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><br/></p><p>同义替换：combine=consistent</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        \r\n        <tr class=\"q-row\">\r\n            <td class=\"q-text-cell\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-q-wrapper\">\r\n                    <span class=\"matrix-num\">17</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"matrix-content\"><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>17</strong> how the depiction of human labour involved danger to an artist</p></div>\r\n                    <button class=\"mini-btn\">🔍</button>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_17\" value=\"A\" data-zyz-question=\"q17\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_17\" value=\"B\" data-zyz-question=\"q17\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_17\" value=\"C\" data-zyz-question=\"q17\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_17\" value=\"D\" data-zyz-question=\"q17\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_17\" value=\"E\" data-zyz-question=\"q17\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_17\" value=\"F\" data-zyz-question=\"q17\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_17\" value=\"G\" data-zyz-question=\"q17\"></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr class=\"ans-row-hidden\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n            <td colspan=\"8\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-analysis\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-key\">✅ 正确答案：B</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-body\"><p>审题：题目问的是哪个段落讲述了艺术家描绘人力劳动时面临危险。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键信息：“human labour”、“danger”和“artist”</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文：B段，“Hine put his own life at risk to photograph workers suspended on cables hundreds of feet in the air, or sitting on a high girder eating lunch.”</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路：文章中B段提到Lewis Hine冒着生命危险去拍摄工人的照片，通过这个事例来表明艺术家描绘人力劳动时面临危险。</p><p><br/></p><p>同义替换：human labour =workers；&nbsp;danger=risk</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        \r\n        <tr class=\"q-row\">\r\n            <td class=\"q-text-cell\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-q-wrapper\">\r\n                    <span class=\"matrix-num\">18</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"matrix-content\"><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>18</strong> a reference to an artist who celebrated a number of unfinished structures</p></div>\r\n                    <button class=\"mini-btn\">🔍</button>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_18\" value=\"A\" data-zyz-question=\"q18\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_18\" value=\"B\" data-zyz-question=\"q18\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_18\" value=\"C\" data-zyz-question=\"q18\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_18\" value=\"D\" data-zyz-question=\"q18\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_18\" value=\"E\" data-zyz-question=\"q18\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_18\" value=\"F\" data-zyz-question=\"q18\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_18\" value=\"G\" data-zyz-question=\"q18\"></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr class=\"ans-row-hidden\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n            <td colspan=\"8\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-analysis\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-key\">✅ 正确答案：F</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-body\"><p>审题：题目问的是哪个段落赞扬了一些未完成结构的艺术家。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键信息：“artist”和“unfinished structures”</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文：F段，“He is perhaps best known for his prints of the Panama Canal as it neared completion and of the partially completed Hell Gate and Delaware River Bridges.”</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路：文章中F段提到Joseph Pennell以描绘接近完工的巴拿马运河和部分完成的Hell Gate和Delaware River桥梁而闻名。</p><p><br/></p><p>同义替换：unfinished structures=partially completed</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        \r\n        <tr class=\"q-row\">\r\n            <td class=\"q-text-cell\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-q-wrapper\">\r\n                    <span class=\"matrix-num\">19</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"matrix-content\"><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>19</strong> a reference to two large engineering works that are symbols of their locations</p></div>\r\n                    <button class=\"mini-btn\">🔍</button>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_19\" value=\"A\" data-zyz-question=\"q19\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_19\" value=\"B\" data-zyz-question=\"q19\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_19\" value=\"C\" data-zyz-question=\"q19\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_19\" value=\"D\" data-zyz-question=\"q19\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_19\" value=\"E\" data-zyz-question=\"q19\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_19\" value=\"F\" data-zyz-question=\"q19\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55356_19\" value=\"G\" data-zyz-question=\"q19\"></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr class=\"ans-row-hidden\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n            <td colspan=\"8\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-analysis\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-key\">✅ 正确答案：A</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-body\"><p>审题：题目问的是哪个段落讲述了两个大型工程作品成为其所在地象征的参考。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键信息：“two large engineering works”和“symbols”</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文：A段，Critics of technology protest against what they see. At the same time, megastructures such as the Brooklyn and Golden Gate Bridges in the US are hailed as majestic human achievements, as well as great engineering monuments that have come to embody the spirit of their respective cities.</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路：文章中A段提到美国的布鲁克林大桥和金门大桥是伟大的人类成就，也是伟大的工程纪念碑，体现了它们各自城市的精神。</p><p><br/></p><p>同义替换：two large engineering works=Brooklyn and Golden Gate Bridges；symbols=spirit</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n        </table>\r\n    </div>\r\n    </div><div class=\"big-section\"><div class=\"group-instruction\"><p><strong><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\">Questions 20 - 22</span></strong></p><p><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><br/></span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\">Choose the correct person </span><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><strong>(A - G)</strong></span><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"> for each statement.&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><br/></span></p><p><strong>List of People</strong></p><p><strong>A</strong> Lewis Hine</p><p><strong>B</strong> Charles Sheeler</p><p><strong>C</strong> Abraham Darby</p><p><strong>D</strong> Michael Rooker</p><p><strong>E</strong> Claude Monet</p><p><strong>F</strong> Joseph Pennell</p><p><strong>G</strong> Santiago Calatrava</p><p><br/></p></div>\r\n    <div class=\"matrix-container\">\r\n        <table>\r\n            <thead><tr><th class=\"corner-header\">Question / Paragraph</th><th>A</th><th>B</th><th>C</th><th>D</th><th>E</th><th>F</th><th>G</th></tr></thead>\r\n            <tbody>\r\n        <tr class=\"q-row\">\r\n            <td class=\"q-text-cell\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-q-wrapper\">\r\n                    <span class=\"matrix-num\">20</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"matrix-content\"><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>20</strong> His engineering constructions are also regarded as works of art.</p></div>\r\n                    <button class=\"mini-btn\">🔍</button>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55516_20\" value=\"A\" data-zyz-question=\"q20\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55516_20\" value=\"B\" data-zyz-question=\"q20\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55516_20\" value=\"C\" data-zyz-question=\"q20\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55516_20\" value=\"D\" data-zyz-question=\"q20\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55516_20\" value=\"E\" data-zyz-question=\"q20\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55516_20\" value=\"F\" data-zyz-question=\"q20\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55516_20\" value=\"G\" data-zyz-question=\"q20\"></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr class=\"ans-row-hidden\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n            <td colspan=\"8\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-analysis\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-key\">✅ 正确答案：G</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-body\"><p>审题：题目问的是哪个学者的工程建筑也被视为艺术作品。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键信息：Santiago Calatrava</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文：G段，Today, one of the most innovative and influential engineers is Santiago Calatrava, who also trained as an architect. His bridges and other structures provide public spaces on a human scale, and stand as pieces of sculpture in their own right.</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路：文章中提到Santiago Calatrava的桥梁和其他结构不仅提供了人性化的公共空间，而且本身就是雕塑作品。</p><p><br/></p><p>同义替换：regarded as=stand as</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        \r\n        <tr class=\"q-row\">\r\n            <td class=\"q-text-cell\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-q-wrapper\">\r\n                    <span class=\"matrix-num\">21</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"matrix-content\"><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>21</strong> He created images of builders constructing an iconic American skyscraper.</p></div>\r\n                    <button class=\"mini-btn\">🔍</button>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55516_21\" value=\"A\" data-zyz-question=\"q21\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55516_21\" value=\"B\" data-zyz-question=\"q21\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55516_21\" value=\"C\" data-zyz-question=\"q21\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55516_21\" value=\"D\" data-zyz-question=\"q21\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55516_21\" value=\"E\" data-zyz-question=\"q21\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55516_21\" value=\"F\" data-zyz-question=\"q21\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55516_21\" value=\"G\" data-zyz-question=\"q21\"></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr class=\"ans-row-hidden\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n            <td colspan=\"8\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-analysis\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-key\">✅ 正确答案：A</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-body\"><p>审题：题目问的是哪个学者创造了建造受欢迎的美国摩天大楼的建筑工人的图像。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键信息：<span style=\"text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">Lewis Hine</span></p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文：B段，“This resulted in a series of striking photographs which have become familiar images of daring. Hine put his own life at risk to photograph workers suspended on cables hundreds of feet in the air, or sitting on a high girder eating lunch.”</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路：文章中提到Lewis Hine拍摄了建造帝国大厦的工人的一系列引人注目的照片。</p><p><br/></p><p>同义替换：builders=workers</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        \r\n        <tr class=\"q-row\">\r\n            <td class=\"q-text-cell\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-q-wrapper\">\r\n                    <span class=\"matrix-num\">22</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"matrix-content\"><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>22</strong> He painted a building connected with a significant innovation in transport.</p></div>\r\n                    <button class=\"mini-btn\">🔍</button>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n            <td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55516_22\" value=\"A\" data-zyz-question=\"q22\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55516_22\" value=\"B\" data-zyz-question=\"q22\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55516_22\" value=\"C\" data-zyz-question=\"q22\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55516_22\" value=\"D\" data-zyz-question=\"q22\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55516_22\" value=\"E\" data-zyz-question=\"q22\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55516_22\" value=\"F\" data-zyz-question=\"q22\"></td><td class=\"radio-cell\"><input type=\"radio\" name=\"q_matrix_55516_22\" value=\"G\" data-zyz-question=\"q22\"></td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        <tr class=\"ans-row-hidden\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n            <td colspan=\"8\">\r\n                <div class=\"matrix-analysis\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-key\">✅ 正确答案：E</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-body\"><p>审题：题目问的是哪个学者画了与交通重要创新相关的建筑。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键信息：<span style=\"text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">Claude Monet</span></p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文：E段，“The Impressionist Claude Monet painted railway stations – such as the Gare St-Lazare in Paris – as well as flower and gardens.&nbsp;”</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路：文章中提到印象派画家Claude Monet画了与铁路相关的建筑，如巴黎的Gare St-Lazare火车站。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </td>\r\n        </tr>\r\n        </tbody>\r\n        </table>\r\n    </div>\r\n    </div><div class=\"big-section\"><div class=\"group-instruction\"><p><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><strong>Questions 23 - 26</strong></span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><br/></span></p><p><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\">Complete the summary. Write </span><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\"><strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS</strong></span><span style=\"font-family: MonospacedNumber, LarkHackSafariFont, LarkEmojiFont, LarkChineseQuote, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Tahoma, &quot;PingFang SC&quot;, &quot;Microsoft Yahei&quot;, Arial, &quot;Hiragino Sans GB&quot;, sans-serif, &quot;Apple Color Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Emoji&quot;, &quot;Segoe UI Symbol&quot;, &quot;Noto Color Emoji&quot;;\">&nbsp;in each gap.</span></p></div>\r\n            <div class=\"q-block normal-q\">\r\n                <div class=\"q-stem\">\r\n                    <span class=\"q-num\">23</span>\r\n                    <div class=\"q-text\"><p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>The iron bridge</strong></p><p>Before the late 18th century, bridges were traditionally constructed of wood and <span class=\"input-blank\" data-question=\"q23\"></span>. Then the engineer <span class=\"input-blank\" data-question=\"q24\"></span> manufactured the elements of an innovative bridge across the <span class=\"input-blank\" data-question=\"q25\"></span>. This iron bridge was the subject of a number of artworks, including a notable one by <span class=\"input-blank\" data-question=\"q26\"></span>. While some may have viewed it as ugly, artists regarded the bridge as a central feature of the landscape.</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                \r\n                <button class=\"btn-toggle\">显示解析</button>\r\n                <div class=\"ans-box\" style=\"display:none;\">\r\n                    <div class=\"ans-row\"><strong>正确答案：</strong> <span class=\"ans-tag\">23</span> stone&nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"ans-tag\">24</span> Abraham Darby&nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"ans-tag\">25</span> River Severn&nbsp;&nbsp;|&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"ans-tag\">26</span> Michael Rooker</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"analysis\">\r\n                <div class=\"sub-analysis-item\">\r\n                    <div class=\"sa-title\">Question 23</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"sa-content\"><p>审题: 题目询问18世纪晚期之前桥梁的主要建筑材料。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键信息: “before the late 18th century”和“wood”</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文: D段，“In the late 18th century, Abraham Darby cast the large iron ribs that formed the world&#39;s first iron bridge, a dramatic departure from the classic stone and timber bridges that dotted the countryside and had been captured in numerous landscape paintings.”。</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路: 原文提到在18世纪晚期之前的传统桥梁是用石头和木材（timber）建造的。</p><p><br/></p><p>同义替换：traditionally =classic</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                \r\n                <div class=\"sub-analysis-item\">\r\n                    <div class=\"sa-title\">Question 24</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"sa-content\"><p>审题: 题目要求填写工程师的名字。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键信息: 关键词是“engineer”和“innovative bridge”</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文: D段，“In the late 18th century, Abraham Darby cast the large iron ribs that formed the world&#39;s first iron bridge, a dramatic departure from the classic stone and timber bridges that dotted the countryside and had been captured in numerous landscape paintings.&quot;</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路: <span style=\"text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">原文提到</span>Abraham Darby是铸造铁桥的大工程师。</p><p><br/></p><p>同义替换：<span style=\"text-wrap-mode: wrap;\">manufactured=formed</span></p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                \r\n                <div class=\"sub-analysis-item\">\r\n                    <div class=\"sa-title\">Question 25</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"sa-content\"><p>审题: 题目要求填写铁桥跨越的河流名称。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键信息: &quot;an innovative bridge&quot;,“across”</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文: D段，“This structure still spans the River Severn, and the Coalbrookdale Museum is crowded with its portraits, showing the iron structure not as a blight on the landscape, but as its focal point.”</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路: 原文提到铁桥跨越的是Severn河。</p><p><br/></p><p>同义替换：central feature=focal point</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                \r\n                <div class=\"sub-analysis-item\">\r\n                    <div class=\"sa-title\">Question 26</div>\r\n                    <div class=\"sa-content\"><p>审题: 题目要求填写某位画家的名字，说明铁桥是多幅艺术作品的主题。</p><p><br/></p><p>定位关键信息: &quot;iron bridge&quot;,“subject of a number of artworks”</p><p><br/></p><p>对应原文: D段，“This is how Michael Rooker shows the iron bridge in his late 18th-century painting, in which the surrounding area radiates out from the bridge and pales behind it.”</p><p><br/></p><p>解题思路: 原文提到迈克尔·鲁克创作了一幅描绘这座铁桥的著名画作。</p></div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n            </div>",
